<subSubSection id="C3736AEC4E13FFEEFF79FC62F972A254" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD639674E13FFEEFF79FC62FB3FA483" blockId="12.[189,310,939,965]" box="[189,310,939,965]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">
<heading id="D09E8E0B4E13FFEEFF79FC62FB3FA483" bold="true" box="[189,310,939,965]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B91DE5754E13FFEEFF79FC62FB3FA483" bold="true" box="[189,310,939,965]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD639674E13FFEEFF79FC13F972A254" blockId="12.[189,1399,986,1298]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">
The new species is close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6942E44E13FFEEFE39FC12F945A4B2" authority="Grichanov, 2004" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2004" box="[509,844,986,1012]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balensis">
<emphasis id="B91DE5754E13FFEEFE39FC12F889A4B2" box="[509,640,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">H. balensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF844964E13FFEEFD43FC13F945A4B2" author="Grichanov I. Ya." box="[647,844,986,1012]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" refId="ref11249" refString="Grichanov I. Ya. 2004. Review of Afrotropical Dolichopodinae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). All-Russian Institute of Plant Protection, St. Petersburg." type="book" year="2004">Grichanov, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6942E44E13FFEEFC43FC12FEEBA4B2" authority="Grichanov, 2004" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2004" box="[903,1250,986,1012]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kefaensis">
<emphasis id="B91DE5754E13FFEEFC43FC12FE1FA4B2" box="[903,1046,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">H. kefaensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF844964E13FFEEFBD8FC13FEEBA4B2" author="Grichanov I. Ya." box="[1052,1250,986,1012]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" refId="ref11249" refString="Grichanov I. Ya. 2004. Review of Afrotropical Dolichopodinae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). All-Russian Institute of Plant Protection, St. Petersburg." type="book" year="2004">Grichanov, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, both known from 
<collectingCountry id="F37E79F74E13FFEEFF38FC37FB6BA35E" box="[252,354,1022,1048]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
, differing distinctly in its larger size, in morphology of the male fore tarsus, antenna, wing and hypopygium. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C6942E44E13FFEEFE6AFBEBF838A37D" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2004" box="[430,561,1057,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balensis">
<emphasis id="B91DE5754E13FFEEFE6AFBEBF838A37D" box="[430,561,1057,1083]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">H. balensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male fore tarsomeres 4–5 dark, with fringe of white erect hairs, 1.5–2 × longer than diameter of tarsomeres; wing with less deep postero-proximal emargination; basoventral lobe of cercus distinctly shorter than mid-ventral lobe; the latter lobe bearing three strong simple setae, half as long as the lobe. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C6942E44E13FFEEFE37FB44F88BA3E1" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2004" box="[499,642,1165,1191]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kefaensis">
<emphasis id="B91DE5754E13FFEEFE37FB44F88BA3E1" box="[499,642,1165,1191]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">H. kefaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the male postpedicel is 2.5–3 × longer than high; fore tarsomere 4–5 dark, with short semi-accumbent dorsal hairs, tarsomere 4 with black hairs and tarsomere 5 with black and white hairs; wing with less deep postero-proximal emargination; mid-ventral lobe of cercus with three strong simple setae, slightly longer than the lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
