<figureCitation id="135225E24E13FFEEFAC8F913FF60A1B3" box="[1292,1385,1754,1781]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,565,1926]" captionTargetId="figure-139@13.[189,1398,565,1929]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 5. Hercostomus vikhrevi sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZMUM). A. Habitus. B. Antenna. C. Fore tarsus. D. Hypopygium, right lateral view. E. Distoventral appendages of epandrium. F. Cercus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4122317" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4122317/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="28">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
